    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>
        "Sukhkarta Dukhharta" is a popular Ganesh aarti that translates to "Salutations to the Lord who is the giver of joy, the remover of sorrow, and the one who eliminates hurdles". The word "sukhkarta" means "giver of joy" and "dukhharta" means "remover of sorrow". The aarti also asks Ganesha to protect devotees in distress and be pleased with them. 
        Saint-poet-philosopher Samarth Ramdas is believed to have written the aarti after seeing the Mayureshwar form of Lord Ganesha at the Morgaon Temple in Pune. You can listen to the aarti on YouTube with English and Hindi lyrics by Shankar Mahadevan.
    </p><br><br>

    <h3>Video</h3>

