    <h2>Description</h2>
    <p>
        Ganesh Utsav, or Ganesh Mahotsav, is a major festival in Maharashtra that originated in Pune in 1893 with Lokmanya Tilak. The festival is a celebration of the community's shared heritage, unity, and devotion, and is more than just a religious event. It's a cultural experience that includes music concerts, traditional dances, cultural performances, and competitions.
        The festival was initially celebrated by a few prominent families in Pune, who installed Ganesh idols in their homes. However, Tilak encouraged the community to come together and build massive public pandals (temporary structures) where large Ganesh idols were installed.
    </p>


